Re: Wanagi

Non sequitur: Affirming the consequent, denying the antecedent, logical inconsistency and, finally, missing the point.
Appeal to ridicule, many questions, personal inconsistency, poisoning the well, social conformance.
Four terms, illicit major, wishful thinking, begging the question.
Appeal to common belief, appeal to authority, false compromise, insignificance, repetition, red herring.
Last but not least, argumentum ad hominem, argumentum ad ignorantium.
